      <td id="content">
        <p><strong>Background</strong><br>Conducted the visual inspection on Piping over water by using DJI Mavic drone which is capable of video recordings per EM request – Ref PO 4410861321 The UAV team for scope mentioned below<br>1. Mr Lim – UAV Pilot in command<br>2. Mr Tan– UAV Co-Pilot<br>3. Mr Lee – UAV Co-Pilot</p><p><br><span style="color:hsl(0,0%,0%);"><strong>Scope of inspection</strong></span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,0%,0%);">Conduct external visual inspection of the pipe support on the trestle (EVI on Trestle 11 ISO Drawing UR-16 and ER 16) with a UAV.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,0%,0%);">All accessible areas inspected and provided findings in this report. EVI was not conducted in areas stated in this report due to accessibility issues. EM Should arrange another alternative method of inspection to ensure 100% inspection</span></p><p><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">Areas unable to inspect</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">1. Pipe 1: Walkway view not accessible due to cable tray along the straight run pipe.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">2. Pipe 7: Drone was not able to attach itself to the pipe to capture information as it is an insulated pipe.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">3. Pipe 8: Drone was not able to attach itself to the pipe to capture information due the contain adjacent pipe to close to each other.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">4. Pipe 9: Drone was not able to attach itself to the pipe to capture information as it is an insulated pipe.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">5. Pipe 10: Due to the paint failure on the surface of the pipe. The Drone was unable to go closer to the contact point.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">6. Pipe 11: Due to the paint failure on the surface of the pipe. The Drone was unable to go closer to the contact point.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">7. Pipe 21: Drone was not able to attach itself to the pipe to capture information as it is an insulated pipe.</span><br><span style="color:hsl(0,75%,60%);">8. Pipe ER-16: Drone was not able to attach itself to the pipe to capture information as it is an insulated pipe.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class="table"><table><tbody><tr><td style="background-color:hsl(210, 75%, 60%);border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;" colspan="2">Conclusion</td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td style="background-color:hsl(210, 75%, 60%);border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;">Report Drafted by:</td><td style="border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;">MOI</td></tr><tr><td style="background-color:hsl(210, 75%, 60%);border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;">Date of Submission:</td><td style="border-bottom:1px solid;border-left:1px solid;border-right:1px solid;border-top:1px solid;">10/9/2020</td></tr></tbody>
        
